        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:55PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 554 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rio Grande, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Point Pleasant, Gallipolis, Henderson, Cheshire, Gallopolis Ferry,
and Lakin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
